"{\n  \"text\": \"Hey everybody, Scotty here, and today I'm going to be pitching a very active compost pile. This is one that's about a week and a half old. The breakdown is going very well, and you'll see lots of steam coming off this thing. But you'll also see lots of unbroken down material and leaves. It's not smelly. That steam is thermophilic bacteria, so it's warming up, but it does not smell like rotten garbage. A lot of people think this will smell like hot garbage. It does not. Smells very fresh and aerobic breakdown. And uh I've been switching between a four-time and a ten tine pitchfork here because they both do the job. The four time is for when it's a little bit rougher. But you'll see a lot of the vegetable matter here uh has not broken down. So I'm gonna put a carbon cap on the edge of this just to make sure it doesn't smell, there's no flies, and this prevents that uh rich nitrogen stuff on the edges from getting too smelly. And you can see after it's all done, I have a nice covered carbon rich or uh carbon capped pile, and we are ready to go. Uh I'm gonna pitch this again tomorrow, but in the meantime, gorgeous pile. Thanks, y'all.\",\n  \"sentences\": [\n    {\n      \"text\": \" Hey everybody, Scotty here, and today I'm going to be pitching a very active compost pile.\",\n      \"start\": 0.32,\n      \"end\": 4.8,\n      \"duration\": 4.48,\n      \"confidence\": 0.992,\n      \"tokens\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \" He\",\n          \"start\": 0.32,\n          \"end\": 0.4,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidence\": 0.995\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"y\",\n          \"start\": 0.4,\n          \"end\": 0.48,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidence\": 0.999\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" ever\",\n          \"start\": 0.56,\n          \"end\": 0.64,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"yb\",\n          \"star